          <ulink url="http://fridrich.blogspot.com/2011/07/libreoffice-visio-import-filter-round.html">Fridrich Strba: LibreOffice Visio import filter - round shapes are beautiful</ulink>
        </title>
        <para>Some might be wondering why the Visio import filter project is so quiet. But the answer is easy: we were busy as bees adding new features.</para>
        <para>You might remember <ulink url="http://fridrich.blogspot.com/2011/06/bounding-box-of-svg-elliptical-arc.html">my blog about the bounding box of an elliptical arc</ulink>. It is because <ulink url="http://www.derivativezero.com/blog/">Eilidh</ulink> added the support of elliptical arcs into <ulink url="http://cgit.freedesktop.org/libreoffice/contrib/libvisio/">libvisio</ulink>. And then we discovered that <ulink url="http://www.libreoffice.org/">LibreOffice</ulink> did not support elliptical arcs in the path at all, just ignored them. Fortunately, there was <ulink url="http://cgit.freedesktop.org/libreoffice/libs-gui/commit/?id=246168e94709a5ea7f34914d8e246af0985a9c81">this patch</ulink> of a hacker extraordinaire, <ulink url="http://blog.thebehrens.net/">Thorsten</ulink> that was used to teach <ulink url="http://www.libreoffice.org/">LibreOffice</ulink> some sane behaviour. (...)</para>
      </blockquote>
      </sect3> -->
